# Day 12 – IAM Access Keys & CLI Authentication (with EC2)

## Goal
Learn how Cloud Support engineers use IAM credentials with AWS CLI on EC2.

## Steps
- Created IAM user with programmatic access.
- Configured AWS CLI on EC2 using access keys.
- Attached `AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess` policy.
- Tested permissions: listed S3 buckets, delete failed as expected.
- Practiced key rotation for security.

## Lessons Learned
- IAM access keys authenticate CLI commands.
- Policies define allowed/denied actions.
- Testing from EC2 simulates real customer environments.
- Key rotation prevents unauthorized access.

